title: National Basketball Association all-time rebounding leaders 1946 to 2020
summary: This is a bar chart representing NBA player in the x axis and Number of rebounds in the y axis.
The Number of rebounds is highest at NBA player Wilt Chamberlain and lowest at NBA player Bill Bridges.
There is a difference of 12870.0 between the maximum NBA player Wilt Chamberlain and minimum NBA player Bill Bridges.

max_summary: This bar chart has 30 columns on the x axis representing NBA player, and Number of rebounds in each NBA player on the y axis.

NBA player Bill Bridges has 2.16 times less Number of rebounds than NBA player Wilt Chamberlain which is the highest.
Number of rebounds at NBA player Wilt Chamberlain is 23924.0 , second place is Bill Russell at 21620.0, and thirdly is Kareem Abdul-Jabbar at 17440.0.
NBA player Charles Barkley, and Charles Oakley have the same Number of rebounds.
The lowest value 11054.0 at Bill Bridges is almost 1.72 times smaller than the average value 13948.8.
Summing up the values of all NBA players, we get total 418464.0.
